README for firefox-bin


RUN AS DIFFERENT USER

  Add the user:
    $ useradd -U -m firefox

  Change the user's appearance:
    $ xhost +SI:localuser:firefox
    $ sudo -u firefox -H lxappearance

  Use this wrapper as firefox launcher:
    #!/bin/sh
    xhost +SI:localuser:firefox
    sudo -u firefox -H /usr/bin/firefox
    # End of file.

   In case of using apulse:
    #!/bin/sh
    xhost +SI:localuser:firefox
    sudo -u firefox -H /usr/bin/apulse /usr/bin/firefox
    # End of file.

  Sudo without a password:
    $ cat > /etc/sudoers.d/firefox <<EOF
    user ALL=(firefox) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/firefox
    EOF

   In case of using apulse:
    $ cat > /etc/sudoers.d/firefox <<EOF
    user ALL=(firefox) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/apulse /usr/bin/firefox
    EOF

    # usermod -aG audio,video firefox

  Use the above wrapper as default firefox launcher:
    $ sudo cp wrapper.sh /opt/bin/firefox

  Export "/opt/bin" before "/usr/bin" in PATH variable, for example:
    export PATH="/bin:/sbin:/opt/bin:/opt/sbin:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin"


FAQ

  Q: Firefox is already running, nut is not responding. To open a new
     window, you must first close the existing Firefox process, or
     restart your computer.

  A: rm ~/.mozilla/firefox/*.default/.parentlock


End of file.
